fr.reflexe.viewshell.api.data

Interface IEdgeProperty<T extends IType>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - property type.
    All Superinterfaces:
    ITranslated

    public interface IEdgeProperty<T extends IType>
extends ITranslated
    Property value for a graph database edge.

    Thread-safety: implementations of this interface are not required to be safe for concurrent access. Therefore, processing should generally not be shared between multiple threads.

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    REFLEXE Technologies

      • setValue

        void setValue(Object value)
        Sets the property value. For non-scalar properties, use a List to set all values in a single operation.

        For any authorization or traceability concerns, the user is implied by the item or by the data structure with which the edge source is associated.

        Parameters:
        value - the value (or list of values), possibly null.
        Throws:
        UnsupportedOperationException - if the value cannot be modified, if the modification is invalid, or if it is unauthorized.
